module.description:
This module is designed for graduate students in mathematics.  It covers the following major topics:
Introduction to convex analysis;  Theory of constrained optimization; Lagrangian duality;  
Algorithms for constrained optimization, in particular, penalty, barrier and augmented Lagrangian methods; Interior-point methods for convex programming, in particular, linear and semidefinite programming.
